<TITLE> Govt halts HSC exams in cyclone-hit centres Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 25 (bdnew24.com)The education ministry has halted the HSC exams scheduled for Tuesday in the cyclone Aila-battered centres, an official said. Subodh Chandra Dhali, public relations officer of the ministry, told bdnews24.com, "We will declare another date for the affected areas where holding examination will not be possible tomorrow (Tuesday)." "Exams will be held in other centres." The chairmen of education boards listed the affected centres in consultation with deputy commissioners of the affected districts. Dhaka board chairman Shamsul Haque said mathematics part 2 and sociology tests were scheduled for Tuesday. bd
